    <stitle>FAN DRIVE CLUTCH: KYSOR 1090 (8000 SERIES) - DISASSEMBLE - CYLINDER REMOVAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CYLINDER REMOVAL</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1200109">Figure 9</hotlnk>for all item numbers in parentheses, unless otherwise stated.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1200109" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1200109" filename="../figg12/G1200109.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. Exploded View</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1.CYLINDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2.CYLINDER NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>3.TAB WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>4.O-RING</callout1>
                <callout1>5.DUST SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>6.HOUSING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>7.FAN STUD</callout1>
                <callout1>8.GREASE SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>9.FAN NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>10.LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>11.FLATWASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>12.SPRING</callout1>
                <callout1>13.SHAFT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>14.O-RING</callout1>
                <callout1>15.PISTON ROD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>16.SNAP RING</callout1>
                <callout1>17.LINING</callout1>
                <callout1>18.RETAINING PLATE(S) (3)</callout1>
                <callout1>19.SCREW</callout1>
                <callout1>20.LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>21.SPRING END CAP</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove cylinder (Item 1,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200109">Figure 9</hotlnk>) attaching hardware (Items 2 and 3) from the center of the
                cylinder and remove the cylinder (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200110">Figure 10</hotlnk>). If the cylinder is difficult to remove, apply 5-10 psi of
                air pressure.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200110" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200110" filename="../figg12/G1200110.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Cylinder Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.HOUSING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.CYLINDER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the cylinder for cracks or scoring on the O-ring surface inside. Replace if found.
                Remove O-ring (Item 14,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200109">Figure 9</hotlnk>) from shoulder inside cylinder. Clean cylinder.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate new O-ring with recommended grease (See
                <hotlnk document="s12001j_HL1200103.xml" xrefid="hl1200103">LUBRICANTS SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>) and
                install on the shoulder inside of the cylinder (Item 1). Set the cylinder aside.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
